{%- comment -%}
  color-schemes — renders one `.color-<id>` rule per merchant colour scheme,
  mapping each scheme onto the theme's existing design tokens. Output goes inside
  a <style> in the layout <head>.

  Each rule sets ONLY the four palette tokens, so any element that reads them
  recolours while everything else stays on tokens.css. scheme-1's defaults equal
  the current palette exactly, so applying `.color-scheme-1` (the default, on
  <body>) is a computed no-op — the storefront is unchanged until a merchant edits
  a scheme or a section opts into a different one. See SCHEMA_GUIDE.md.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- for scheme in settings.color_schemes -%}
.color-{{ scheme.id }}{
  --bg: {{ scheme.settings.background }};
  --text: {{ scheme.settings.text }};
  --surface: {{ scheme.settings.surface }};
  --line: {{ scheme.settings.line }};
}
{% endfor -%}
